

The numbers are placed in the usual Ulam (square) spiral :

\[
\begin{matrix}
\cdots &5&4&3&\cdots\\
\cdots &6&1&2&\cdots\\
\cdots &7&8&9&\cdots
\end{matrix}
\]

Hence  

* 1 is at \((0,0)\);
* 2 is at \((1,0)\);
* 3 at \((1,1)\);
* 4 at \((0,1)\);
* 5 at \((-1,1)\); … etc.

---

### 1.  Which “ring’’ contains 2026?

For the \(k\)-th ring (the set of points with \(\max(|x|,|y|)=k\))

\[
(2k+1)^2\text{ is at }(k,-k)
\]

and contains the numbers from \((2k-1)^2+1\) up to \((2k+1)^2\).

\[
45^2=2025=(2\cdot22+1)^2 .
\]

Thus the ring \(k=22\) ends at 2025, placed at \((22,-22)\).
The next number, 2026, is the first point of the next ring:

\[
2026\; \text{at}\;(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  Coordinates of the eight neighbours

The eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\) are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
&(22,-22)\qquad &&(24,-22)\\
&(23,-21)\qquad &&(23,-23)\\
&(22,-21)\qquad &&(24,-21)\\
&(22,-23)\qquad &&(24,-23)
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3.  From coordinates to the corresponding numbers  

For a point \((x,y)\) let  
\(L=\max(|x|,|y|)\) and \(M(L)=(2L+1)^2\).
The Ulam‑spiral gives

* Bottom side (\(y=-L\)) :   \(n=M-(L-x)\);
* Left side (\(x=-L\))   :   \(n=M-(3L+y)\);
* Top side (\(y=L\))    :   \(n=M-(5L+x)\);
* Right side (\(x=L\) and \(y>-L\)): \(n=M-7L+y\).

Applying these formulas:

| neighbour | \((x,y)\) | \(L\) | formula | value |
|-----------|-----------|-------|---------|-------|
| West      | (22,‑22)  | 22    | bottom  | \(2025\) |
| East      | (24,‑22)  | 24    | right   | \(2401-7·24-22=2211\) |
| North     | (23,‑21)  | 23    | right   | \(2209-7·23-21=2027\) |
| South     | (23,‑23)  | 23    | bottom  | \(2209\) |
| NW        | (22,‑21)  | 22    | right   | \(2025-7·22-21=1850\) |
| NE        | (24,‑21)  | 24    | right   | \(2401-7·24-21=2212\) |
| SW        | (22,‑23)  | 23    | bottom  | \(2209- (23-22)=2208\) |
| SE        | (24,‑23)  | 24    | right   | \(2401-7·24-23=2210\) |

Thus the eight neighbours are  

\[
2025,\;2211,\;2027,\;2209,\;1850,\;2212,\;2208,\;2210 .
\]

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
S&=2025+2211+2027+2209+1850+2212+2208+2210\\
  &=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
